- 'Average speed' is the mean velocity over a period or distance;
- 'Weather conditions' and 'road surfaces' are factors that can significantly affect vehicle performance;
- 'Simulation scenarios' are virtual environments designed to test vehicle behavior under different conditions.

- "Out-of-bounds occurrences" refer to instances where the vehicle's trajectory deviates from the designated path or area during the simulation;
- "Average velocity" is the mean speed of the vehicle over the course of the simulation;
- A "completed" simulation run indicates that the simulation has finished successfully;
- "Viewed" access type means the user has accessed the simulation data for viewing purposes.

- 'Vessels' refers to vehicle models;
- 'Sailed through more than five completed voyages' means the total number of distinct completed simulation runs is greater than 5;
- 'Average duration of their journeys' refers to the average simulation time calculated as the difference between the end time and start time of the simulation runs;
- 'Voyages' refers to simulation runs;
- 'List these vessels in the order of the longest voyages first' means the results are ordered by average simulation time in descending order.

- 'Rain', 'Snow', and 'Sunny' are weather conditions that can affect the performance of vehicle models in simulations;
- `run_id` uniquely identifies each simulation run;
- `model_name` represents the name of the vehicle model being tested.

- "steering input" refers to the control signal sent to the vehicle's steering system;
- "average velocity" is calculated in kilometers per hour (km/h);
- The results are ordered from the highest to the lowest average speed.
